# AnimePlatform

A full-stack anime platform inspired by azuki.com, hianime.to, and myanimelist.net.

- Next.js 14 (App Router)
- Tailwind CSS
- TypeScript
- Dark/Light mode + 5 theme engine (placeholder)
- Falling sakura background
- Custom logo
- Homepage with Anime, Manga, Manhwa, Marketplace sections

## Getting Started

```bash
npm install
npm run dev

## Authentication

- **NextAuth.js** for authentication.
- Supports **Google**, **Email**, and **Web3 Wallet** login.
- Rate-limiting to prevent spam and fake logins.
- User session data is stored securely using Prisma.

### Environment Variables

Make sure to set the following environment variables in your `.env.local`:

```env
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_google_client_secret
EMAIL_SERVER=smtp://user:pass@smtp.example.com:587
EMAIL_FROM=your_email@example.com

## Anime & Manga Catalog

- Horizontally scrollable image gallery for Anime, Manga, and Manhwa.
- Responsive, multi-row carousel using `react-slick`.
- Users can rate and comment on items (only logged-in users).
- Detailed pages for each item with descriptions and images.

### Features

- Smooth scroll with drag or arrow buttons.
- Click to open detailed page.

## Streaming Player

- Custom video player with play/pause, volume control, quality toggle, and fullscreen.
- Episode selection dropdown or sidebar.
- Comments section for user interaction.
- 403 bypass placeholder for proxying public links.

### Features

- Supports M3U8 and MP4 streaming links.
- Displays anime title and episode information.

## Forum

- Reddit-style forum for anime discussion.
- Rich text editor for new posts using `react-quill`.
- Users can upvote/downvote, reply, and edit/delete their posts.
- Categories for discussions (e.g., Anime Talk, Manga News, Fan Art, Help).
- Real-time updates using SWR.
- Infinite scroll or pagination for posts.

### Features

- Only logged-in users can post or comment.

## Marketplace

- Owner-only listings for products.
- Products shown in USD.
- Payment support via:
  - Stripe (Card)
  - Web3 wallets (Crypto payments)
  - UPI (India) via Razorpay or equivalent
- Checkout flow with:
  - Product page
  - Quantity selection
  - Address panel with user info
  - Payment selection
  - Order success screen
- Admin panel for managing products and orders.

### Features

- Users can view and purchase products.
- Admins can add, delete, and manage products.

## Theme System

- Five visual themes:
  - Retro Pixel
  - Sakura Blossom
  - Cyberpunk Neon
  - Minimal Light
  - Cozy Cafe
- Each theme includes:
  - Layout changes
  - Typography styles
  - Card structure and animations
  - Color palettes
- Theme switcher panel in the hamburger menu.
- Theme previews shown for selection.
- Global state management for theme application.

# AnimePlatform

A full-stack anime platform featuring a marketplace, forum, and streaming player.

## Features

- Anime, Manga, and Manhwa catalog
- User authentication with NextAuth.js
- Marketplace with payment support via Stripe and Web3 wallets
- Forum for discussions
- Theme system with multiple visual themes

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js (>= 14.x)
- npm or yarn
- A database (e.g., PostgreSQL, MySQL, SQLite)

### Installation

1. Clone the repository:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/Serenawaifu/symmetrical-garbanzo
   cd symmetrical-garbanzo

